Following the architectural blueprint you laid out, we will construct the core engine and data foundation. This initial version will focus on implementing the fundamental logarithmic zoom mechanic using Svelte, D3.js, and Three.js, with placeholder assets.

### Step 1: Project Setup

First, let's set up the SvelteKit project and install the necessary dependencies as defined in your blueprint.

Open your terminal and run the following commands:

```bash
# 1. Create a new SvelteKit project (select Skeleton project, Yes to TypeScript)
npm create svelte@latest harmonic-cosmos
cd harmonic-cosmos

# 2. Install the core dependencies from the blueprint
npm install three d3-scale

# 3. Install TypeScript type definitions for our libraries
npm install --save-dev @types/three @types/d3-scale

# 4. Install the project dependencies
npm install

# 5. (Optional) Initialize a git repository
git init && git add -A && git commit -m "Initial commit"
```

### Step 2: File Structure

We will create a logical structure within the `src/lib` directory to organize our code. This structure directly reflects the components of the UHT pipeline.

```
harmonic-cosmos/
└── src/
    └── lib/
        ├── components/
        │   ├── CosmicCanvas.svelte  # The Three.js rendering engine
        │   └── ZoomSlider.svelte    # The logarithmic UI slider
        ├── core/
